We got my grandmother an Air Conditioner this winter, as otherwise she has to live in the fireplace-heated basement and gets depressed in the long months of cold.

She treats it like a living organism, like an animal. Recently it broke and stopped working and she just waited...

...for it to "decide" to start working again, like it is a conscious creature. She studies how its work responds to the weather and temperature outside - it's very interesting. She does not know that machines do not have souls - or do they? Luv my grandma, reminder to call yours!
